ructure</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.SavedState\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">SavedState</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Backtrackable state for the `TermElabM` monad.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.SavedState","kind":"structure","line":618,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.SavedState","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.lean#L618-L623"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.bindMutVarsFromTuple\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">bindMutVarsFromTuple</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">vars</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Name</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">tupleVar</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.FVarId\">FVarId</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElabM\">DoElabM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElabM\">DoElabM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a list of mut vars `vars` and an FVar `tupleVar` binding a tuple, bind the mut vars to the\nfields of the tuple and call `k` in the resulting local context.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.bindMutVarsFromTuple","kind":"def","line":589,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.bindMutVarsFromTuple","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.lean#L589-L616"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.registerMutVarAlias\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">registerMutVarAlias</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Name</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElabM\">DoElabM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `x` is a `mut` variable, record that its current binding aliases the original `let mut` binding,\nso that go-to-definition and find-references treat both as the same variable.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.registerMutVarAlias","kind":"def","line":579,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.registerMutVarAlias","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.lean#L579-L587"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont.withDeadCodeFromInfo\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">DoElemCont</span>.<span class=\"name\">withDeadCodeFromInfo</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">dec</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont\">DoElemCont</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">info</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.html#Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo\">ControlInfo</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont\">DoElemCont</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Wrap `dec.k` so it elaborates as dead iff `info.noFallthrough`. ","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont.withDeadCodeFromInfo","kind":"def","line":575,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont.withDeadCodeFromInfo","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.lean#L575-L577"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont.elabAsSyntacticallyDeadCode\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">DoElemCont</span>.<span class=\"name\">elabAsSyntacticallyDeadCode</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">dec</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont\">DoElemCont</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElabM\">DoElabM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Elaborate the `DoElemCont` with the `deadCode` flag set to `deadSyntactically` to emit warnings. ","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont.elabAsSyntacticallyDeadCode","kind":"def","line":563,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont.elabAsSyntacticallyDeadCode","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.lean#L563-L573"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont.continueWithUnit\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">DoElemCont</span>.<span class=\"name\">continueWithUnit</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">dec</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont\">DoElemCont</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElabM\">DoElabM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Return `let $k.resultName : PUnit := PUnit.unit; $(← k.k)`, ensuring that the result type of `k.k`\nis `PUnit` and then immediately zeta-reduce the `let`.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont.continueWithUnit","kind":"def","line":554,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont.continueWithUnit","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.lean#L554-L561"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont.mkBindUnlessPure\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">DoElemCont</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkBindUnlessPure</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">dec</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont\">DoElemCont</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElabM\">DoElabM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Return `$e >>= fun ($dec.resultName : $dec.resultType) => $(← dec.k)`, cancelling\nthe bind if `$(← dec.k)` is `pure $dec.resultName` or `e` is some `pure` computation.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont.mkBindUnlessPure","kind":"def","line":508,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont.mkBindUnlessPure","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.lean#L508-L552"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont.ensureUnit\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">DoElemCont</span>.<span class=\"name\">ensureUnit</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">dec</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont\">DoElemCont</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElabM\">DoElabM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont\">DoElemCont</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a continuation `dec`, returns a continuation derived from `dec` with result type `PUnit`.\nIf `dec` already has result type `PUnit`, simply returns `dec`. Otherwise, an error is logged and a\nnew continuation is returned that calls `dec` with `sorry` as a result.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont.ensureUnit","kind":"def","line":500,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont.ensureUnit","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.lean#L500-L506"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont.ensureUnitAt\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">DoElemCont</span>.<span class=\"name\">ensureUnitAt</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">dec</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont\">DoElemCont</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">ref</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Syntax\">Syntax</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElabM\">DoElabM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont\">DoElemCont</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a continuation `dec` and a reference `ref`, returns a continuation derived from `dec` with result type `PUnit`.\nIf `dec` already has result type `PUnit`, simply returns `dec`. Otherwise, an error is logged and a\nnew continuation is returned that calls `dec` with `sorry` as a result. The error is reported at `ref`.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont.ensureUnitAt","kind":"def","line":492,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont.ensureUnitAt","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.lean#L492-L498"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont.ensureHasTypeAt\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">DoElemCont</span>.<span class=\"name\">ensureHasTypeAt</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">dec</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont\">DoElemCont</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">ref</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Syntax\">Syntax</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">elementType</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElabM\">DoElabM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont\">DoElemCont</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a continuation `dec`, a reference `ref`, and an element result type `elementType`, returns a\ncontinuation derived from `dec` with result type `elementType`.\nIf `dec` already has result type `elementType`, simply returns `dec`.\nOtherwise, an error is logged and a new continuation is returned that calls `dec` with `sorry` as a\nresult. The error is reported at `ref`.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont.ensureHasTypeAt","kind":"def","line":469,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.DoElemCont.ensureHasTypeAt","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.lean#L469-L490"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.mkMonadicResultTypeMismatchError\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkMonadicResultTypeMismatchError</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">contType </span><span class=\"fn\">elementType</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Message.html#Lean.MessageData\">MessageData</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.mkMonadicResultTypeMismatchError","kind":"def","line":465,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.mkMonadicResultTypeMismatchError","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.lean#L465-L467"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.withLCtxKeepingMutVarDefs\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">withLCtxKeepingMutVarDefs</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">oldLCtx</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/LocalContext.html#Lean.LocalContext\">LocalContext</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">oldCtx</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.Context\">Context</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">resultName</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Name</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElabM\">DoElabM</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElabM\">DoElabM</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Restores the local context to `oldCtx` and adds the new reaching definitions of the mut vars and\nresult. Then resume the continuation `k` with the `mutVars` restored to the given `oldMutVars`.\n\nThis function is useful to de-nest\n```\nlet mut x := 0\nlet y := 3\nlet z ← do\n  let mut y ← e\n  x := y + 1\n  pure y\nlet y := y + 3\npure (x + y + z)\n```\ninto\n```\nlet mut x := 0\nlet y := 3\nlet mut y† ← e\nx := y† + 1\nlet z ← pure y†\nlet y := y + 3\npure (x + y + z)\n```\nNote that the continuation of the `let z ← ...` bind, roughly\n``k := .cont `z _ `(let y := y + 3; pure (x + y + z))``,\nneeds to be elaborated in a local context that contains the reassignment of `x`, but not the shadowing\nmut var definition of `y`.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.withLCtxKeepingMutVarDefs","kind":"def","line":425,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.withLCtxKeepingMutVarDefs","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.lean#L425-L463"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.getReassignedMutVars\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">getReassignedMutVars</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">rootCtx</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/LocalContext.html#Lean.LocalContext\">LocalContext</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">mutVars</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Data/HashSet/Basic.html#Std.HashSet\">Std.HashSet</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Name</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">childCtxs</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> <a href=\"./Lean/LocalContext.html#Lean.LocalContext\">LocalContext</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Data/HashSet/Basic.html#Std.HashSet\">Std.HashSet</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Name</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The subset of `mutVars` that were reassigned in any of the `childCtxs` relative to the given\n`rootCtx`.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.getReassignedMutVars","kind":"def","line":395,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.getReassignedMutVars","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.lean#L395-L404"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.withDeadCode\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">withDeadCode</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">deadCode</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.CodeLiveness\">CodeLiveness</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElabM\">DoElabM</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElabM\">DoElabM</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.withDeadCode","kind":"def","line":392,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.withDeadCode","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.lean#L392-L393"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.map1TermElabM\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">map1TermElabM</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">β</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Sort</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>} → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">β</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM\">TermElabM</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>)</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM\">TermElabM</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">β</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElabM\">DoElabM</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.DoElabM\">DoElabM</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Do.map1TermElabM","kind":"def","line":388,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.map1TermElabM","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Basic.lean#L388-L390